21/03/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Menduh Thaci was re-elected as leader of the opposition Democratic Party of Albanians (DPA) at the party's congress Sunday (March 20th) in Tetovo. 
His nomination was supported by 600 delegates. 
Thaci said that his party is ready for early elections whenever they are called. 
The DPA blames the ruling VMRO-DPMNE for neglecting the rights of Albanians and insists on speeding up the EU and NATO accession processes. 
(Sitel, MTV, Deutsche Welle - 20/03/11)
